    {
      "sort": 500000,
      "name": "Chat Avatar",
      "type": "text",
      "_id": "9zjUHF8vJDUMovDd",
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>This System Setting is only available for the Gamemaster and will be set globally for every player. There are two options:</p><p><strong>1. Avatar of the Configuration</strong></p><p>if this setting is chosen, every chat message will show the configured image set up in the config menu. </p><img src=\"systems/ed4e/assets/manual/settings/chat-avatar-config.PNG\" class=\"centered\" /><p><strong>2. Avatar of the Token</strong></p><p>If this setting is chosen, it will for every chat message a player creates, use either the token image of the owned token if the player has the token selected, or will use the character portrait if no or another (not owned by the player) token is selected.</p><p>This is similar for Gamemaster, but since the GM is not owning any (or all) tokens, the chat message will either show the selected token, or use the Avatar from the configuration as a fallback.</p>",
        "markdown": ""
      },
