      "name": "Circle enhancement talent Requirment",
      "type": "text",
      "_id": "6m38q7t9a3UFE5Bq",
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 2
      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>this setting has three options:</p><p><strong>1. Discipline Talents to Advance</strong></p><p>this settings enables the rules described on page 452 of the Players Guide</p><p><strong>2. All talents to Advance</strong></p><p>this setting enables the rules described on page 453 of the Players Guide</p><p><strong>3. All talents to Advance - House Rule</strong></p><p>this setting enables the house rule which works similar to the All Talents to Advance Optional Rule, with the following differences shown in the table. It is basically a mixture from standard and all talents to advance. It has the flexibility, but keeps the requirement of the number of talents on the tier level</p><p>Â </p><table border=\"1\"><colgroup><col></col><col></col><col></col><col></col><col></col><col></col></colgroup><tbody><tr style=\"background-color:rgb(149, 165, 166)\"><td>New Circle</td><td>Min Novice Talents</td><td>Min Journeyman Talents</td><td>min Warden Talents</td><td>Min Master Taletns</td><td>Min rank of all required Talents</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>5</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>2</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>6</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>3</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>7</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td>8</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>5</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td>8</td><td>1</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>6</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td>8</td><td>2</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>7</td></tr><tr><td>8</td><td>8</td><td>3</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>8</td></tr><tr><td>9</td><td>8</td><td>4</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>9</td></tr><tr><td>10</td><td>8</td><td>4</td><td>1</td><td>0</td><td>10</td></tr><tr><td>11</td><td>8</td><td>4</td><td>2</td><td>0</td><td>11</td></tr><tr><td>12</td><td>8</td><td>4</td><td>3</td><td>0</td><td>12</td></tr><tr><td>13</td><td>8</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>0</td><td>13</td></tr><tr><td>14</td><td>8</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>1</td><td>14</td></tr><tr><td>15</td><td>8</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>2</td><td>15</td></tr></tbody></table>",
